  "prompt": "Why do people make fun of Dory the fish in Finding Nemo?",
  "response": "People often make fun of Dory the fish in \"Finding Nemo\" primarily because of her forgetfulness. Dory, voiced by Ellen DeGeneres, has short-term memory loss, which leads to humorous situations where she forgets things almost instantly. Her constant, comedic misunderstandings and repetition of events make her an easy target for light-hearted jokes and amusement from both the other characters in the movie and the audience. Despite this, Dory is beloved for her optimistic and caring nature, and her character adds plenty of humor and warmth to the story.",
